review_blob:
Mother of god! 
If you ever had a chance to try this, dont hesitate. This is gonna blow you out.

Looks like its the best beer available at your local grocery in Poland, though it has this urinary finish, like all the ywiec beers. But it reminds you of the good beers youve drunk in the past and its only 0,75. 0,75! (0,75) zero-point-seventy-five-euro. True story
Quick deScription: take dull eurolager, mix with ipa 50:50 and youll get this one. Sounds encouraging?
When cold iIts much more weizen rather than ipa, after warm-up the situation changes nearly 180 degrees. So you start with weizen and end up with ipa, which is quite unique but not very interesting.

Looks like its my fav - kicks ass in every category, every aspect of this beer can be concluded with the rich word. There is so much going on in your mouth you dont feel all this IBU 100, as well as 9% of alcohol. Stands out.
Great first impression - strong, cloudy amber colour and rich fruity aroma. Could be more bitter. Finish is problematic - too long and really uncool.

This one is confusing. Nice, huge beige head, and cola-like colour. Slight aroma, little bit like chocolate mixed with rubber, unfortunately. Taste is atypical, gentle, not bitter at all while drinking, but after all leaves some bitterness. Nothing exceptional, but there is something inside

Typical polish AIPA, rich mango aroma, well-balances fruits and bitterness. 
However, theres not much to make you buy it again. Pros: big head, quite strong. Cons: ugliest layout in the market.
